---
import { heroFacts } from '../data/site';
import BackgroundTreatment from './BackgroundTreatment.astro';
---

<section class="relative overflow-hidden border-b border-[rgba(36,27,23,0.12)]">
  <BackgroundTreatment variant="hero" />
  <div class="section-shell relative grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_20rem] lg:items-start">
    <div class="max-w-4xl">
      <p class="eyebrow">Scholarship, strategy, and systems</p>
      <h1 class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-[1.95rem] leading-[0.98] md:text-[2.8rem]">
        How power gets made, documented, and lived.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-[1.08rem] leading-8 text-slate-100">
        Martin Lepage is a Montreal-based scholar, writer, and AI governance strategist working across governance,
        culture, and public writing.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-2xl text-base text-slate-300">
        Across advisory work, research, and essays, the main question is simple: how does power become believable,
        and what do people experience once it becomes real?
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a class="button-primary" href="/projects/">View governance work</a>
        <a class="button-secondary" href="/papers/">Read publications</a>
      </div>
      <ul class="bullet-links mt-6">
        <li><a class="link-inline" href="/resume/">View resume</a></li>
        <li><a class="link-inline" href="/contact/">Contact</a></li>
      </ul>
      <ul class="bullet-facts mt-8">
        {heroFacts.map((fact) => (
          <li>{fact}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>

    <aside class="veil-panel space-y-4 lg:mt-10 lg:pl-2">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Start here</p>
        <h2 class="mt-4 text-[1.2rem] md:text-[1.36rem]">Governance first, with research and writing alongside it.</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-7 text-slate-200">
          Governance teams usually start with projects, the resume, or contact. Academic and editorial readers can move
          directly into publications, writings, and talks.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ul class="bullet-links">
        <li><a class="link-inline" href="/projects/">Governance projects and practice</a></li>
        <li><a class="link-inline" href="/resume/">Resume and CV</a></li>
        <li><a class="link-inline" href="/papers/">Publications and talks</a></li>
        <li><a class="link-inline" href="/writing/">Writings and books</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>
